%N A390928 Array listed by rows: row n is the primitive Pythagorean triple a < b < c with least perimeter a+b+c such that its inradius (a+b-c)/2 = n.
%C A390928 A primitive Pythagorean triple is [x^2-y^2, 2*x*y, x^2+y^2] (or [2*x*y, x^2-y^2, x^2+y^2] if x^2-y^2 > 2*x*y) where x > y are coprime and exactly one of them is odd.
%C A390928 Its inradius is (x-y)*y.
%H A390928 Robert Israel, <a href="/A390928/b390928.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10002</a> (rows 1 .. 3334, flattened)
%F A390928 T(n,3) = A087484(n).
